review_blob: bottled - very little aroma, peppery malty taste and a little citrus or herbs followed by the hoppy bitterness.  its a decent beer not bad, not great.
this beer smells just like The Beast - but the taste is no comparison.  Pours nice dark brown color, nice foamy head.  Tastes like a  sweet porter.  blah blah blah.  its ok for 4.99.
tastes great!  like drinking a glass of brown sugar.............................................
beer_name: Avery The Beast Grand Cru Ale

review_blob: its got a good stout nose on it.  Coffee, licorish (sp?) & rubbing alcohol.  looks really great.  black as midnight.  has STRONG alcohol flavor comes through immediately, followed by dark chocolate and coffee.
this beer smells really good. fruity - plums, cherries, figs.  appearance is great too.  nice dark color.  the taste is weaker than i anticipated.  sorry.... gotta go.

ok - here goes.  it doesnt have much of an aroma.  sort of beerish aroma with a hint of ass.  sorry, i dont know.  the appearance is very nice, like a nice round ass.  its a hazy orange/brown color, like the wrinkly sphincter of an asian womans ass.  good flavor -  sweet with bitter hops and ass.  feels really good in my mouth and leaves a good hoppy coating - reminiscent of my wifes pasty white ass.

damn fine beer.  ill work on writing better reviews over time.  im tempted to say "starts with a burst of pine hops - but thats because it does and that what the reviewer before me wrote.  so, fuck it, thats what im gonna say.  nice hazy orangish amber appearance. nice head when ya pour it right.  and there IS some chemical taste to it too.... kind of funky ... good shit though... cant live without Alpha King....
